---

## Priority 1: Complete the Base 13 Workbench Components

The Workbench shell tree has 13 nodes. Currently only 3 have TSX implementations
(Workbench, ContentPanel, StringControl). The remaining 10 are the core application
chrome that every page needs.

### NavigationSidebar group (7 components)

- **NavigationSidebar** — vertical sidebar drawer, collapsible, contains header/content/footer slots
- **SidebarHeader** — top-pinned container, holds the HamburgerToggle
- **HamburgerToggle** — drawer expand/collapse button
- **SidebarContent** — scrollable middle area, conditionally renders NavigationTreeView (standard) or ObjectTreeView (dev mode)
- **NavigationTreeView** — hierarchical route list, role-masked, reads from `system_objects_routes`
- **SidebarFooter** — bottom-pinned container, holds login/user/devmode controls

### Footer controls (2 components)

- **DevModeToggle** — switches sidebar between standard and dev mode, ROLE_SERVICE_ADMIN only
- **LoginControl** — OAuth login widget, renders login button or authenticated state
- **UserProfileControl** — user avatar/name display, logout action

### Dev mode (1 component)

- **ObjectTreeView** — live browsable view of the object tree (all `system_objects_*` tables), lazy-loaded by category

### Sequencing

1. NavigationSidebar + SidebarHeader + SidebarContent + SidebarFooter (structural containers — just layout, render children)
2. HamburgerToggle (drawer collapse state)
3. NavigationTreeView (reads routes, renders navigation items)
4. LoginControl + UserProfileControl (auth integration — depends on existing auth module)
5. DevModeToggle (state toggle, role-gated)
6. ObjectTreeView (dev mode — reads from object tree tables)

Steps 1-2 are trivial layout components. Step 3 needs an RPC call to load routes.
Steps 4 need auth module integration. Steps 5-6 need state management for mode switching.

