## Priority 2: Object Tree Editor UI — The ObjectEditor Panels

When dev mode is active and the ObjectEditor loads for a page definition, it should
present five panels:

### 2a. Component Builder (tree editor)

The main editing surface. Shows the page's component tree as an interactive tree view.
Drag-to-reorder, click-to-select. Selected node's properties appear in the Properties panel.
Add/remove nodes via the Toolbox. This is a filtered view of `system_objects_component_tree`
scoped to one page's `ref_page_guid`.

### 2b. Page Context Object Tree (component subtree)

A read-only reference view showing the current page's tree structure with component
names, sequences, labels, and field bindings. Distinct from the Component Builder in
that it's a display panel, not an editor. Think of it as the "outline" view alongside
the visual editor.

### 2c. Toolbox (component palette)

A dropdown or searchable list of all registered components from `system_objects_components`.
Select a component type, click "Insert" — a new tree node gets created as a child of
the currently selected node in the Component Builder. The Toolbox reads from the
component registry and groups by `pub_category` (page, section, grid, control).

### 2d. Properties Panel

When a tree node is selected in the Component Builder, the Properties Panel shows
its editable attributes: label, fieldBinding, sequence, and any component-specific
directives (color, size, visibility hints). This panel is itself composed of sub-elements —
StringControls for text fields, IntControls for sequence, BoolToggles for flags,
DropdownSelects for enum values, color pickers for style directives.

Data bindings are also defined here — the designer sets the source type (literal, config,
column, function), provides the value or selects the source, and sets the alias. When
a data binding changes, the ComponentBuilder dispatches to the ContractQueryBuilder.

### 2e. Query Preview + Data Model Preview

Two read-only panels showing the ContractQueryBuilder's output:

- **Query Preview** — displays the derived SQL query text (or "No query — all static values" for literal-only pages). This is the actual query that will be stored and executed.
- **Data Model Preview** — displays the derived output model: field names, types, sources. Shows the input model if the page has parameterized queries.

These panels update live when the ContractQueryBuilder returns analysis results after
binding changes.

